// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// VitaTrack — Vitals Hub (ESP32 Dev Module)
// MAX30102 (HR+SpO2) | SSD1306 OLED | Dual WiFi (AP+STA)
// BLE (respiration belt) | SPIFFS offline queue | Flask POST
//
// ── Architecture ──────────────────────────────────────────────
// AP  : "VitaTrack-Hub"  password = Device ID (e.g. "ESP32-001")
//       Temp + Belt modules connect here and POST their data
//       Hub stores received data in memory
//
// STA : Connects to hospital/home WiFi for internet
//       Every 60s: posts all vitals to Flask server
//
// ── Config ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Hold BOOT (GPIO0) 3s → captive portal for internet WiFi setup
//   Connect to "VitaTrack-Hub-Setup" / "vitatrack"
//   Open any URL or type 192.168.4.1
//   Fields: Device ID, Flask URL, WiFi SSID, WiFi Password
//
// ── Module pairing ────────────────────────────────────────────
// Hub AP password = Hub Device ID
// Modules connect using that password by default
// To re-pair: use IP scanner to find module IP on hub network,
//   open http://<module-ip> in browser, change hub password
//
// Libraries: SparkFun MAX3010x, Adafruit SSD1306/GFX,
//            NimBLE-Arduino, ArduinoJson
//            DNSServer — built-in, no install needed
// Partition: Huge APP (3MB No OTA / 1MB SPIFFS)
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

